casebody.data:
Joe JONES, Appellant, v. A. C. ADERHOLD, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Atlanta, Georgia, Appellee. No. 6784. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 13, 1933. Joe Jones, in pro. per. Clint W. Hager, U. S. Atty., and Hal Lindsay, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Atlanta, Ga., for appellee.

Before BRYAN, SIBLEY, and HUTCHESON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
